## Database query optimization (Drizzle / Neon)

### 1. Always bound reads

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD: explicit `.limit(...)` / keyset pagination
await db.select().from(projects).where(eq(projects.uid, uid)).limit(20);

// ❌ BAD: unbounded `.select()` on large tables
await db.select().from(projects);
```

### 2. Select only needed columns

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD: column projection
await db
  .select({ id: projects.id, name: projects.name })
  .from(projects)
  .limit(20);

// ⚠️ Avoid pulling large JSON blobs unless the UI needs them
```

### 3. Prefer joins or batched queries over N+1 loops

Fetch related rows in one query (Drizzle `with` / explicit joins) instead of per-row queries inside `map`.

### 4. Fetch on the server by default

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD: Server Component + Drizzle
import { getDbHttp } from '@repo/db';
import { projects } from '@repo/db/schema';

export default async function ProjectsPage() {
  const db = getDbHttp();
  const rows = await db.select().from(projects).limit(20);
  return <ProjectList projects={rows} />;
}
```

