## Image and Media Optimization

### 1. Next.js Image Component

**Always use Next.js Image for images:**

```typescript
import Image from 'next/image';

// ✅ GOOD: Optimized image with proper sizing
<Image
  src={imageUrl}
  alt="Description"
  width={800}
  height={600}
  priority={isAboveFold} // For LCP optimization
  loading={isAboveFold ? undefined : 'lazy'}
/>

// ❌ BAD: Native img tag
<img src={imageUrl} alt="Description" />
```

**Benefits:**
- Automatic WebP/AVIF conversion
- Responsive image generation
- Lazy loading
- Blur placeholder support

### 2. External Image Domains

**Configure external image domains in `next.config.js`:**

```typescript
// next.config.js
export default {
  images: {
    remotePatterns: [
      {
        protocol: 'https',
        hostname: 'your-r2-domain.com',
        pathname: '/**',
      },
    ],
  },
};
```

### 3. R2 Public URLs

**Use helper function for R2 URLs:**

```typescript
import { getR2PublicUrl } from '@/lib/utils/r2';

// ✅ GOOD: Consistent URL generation
const imageUrl = getR2PublicUrl(mediaKey);

// ❌ BAD: Hardcoded URLs
const imageUrl = `https://r2-domain.com/${mediaKey}`;
```

### 4. Video Optimization

**Use proper video attributes:**

```typescript
<video
  src={videoUrl}
  controls
  preload="metadata" // Don't preload entire video
  poster={thumbnailUrl} // Show thumbnail while loading
/>
```

